📘 README 3 — Case 3 (Redis + Replica + Master + Nginx)
# 🚀 Case 3: Production Architecture (Redis + Replica + Master + Nginx)

---

## 📌 Overview
Production system:
- Redis → cache
- Replica → reads
- Master → writes
- Nginx → frontend

---

## 🧱 Architecture


Browser → Nginx → Flask API
→ Redis (fast)
→ Replica (fallback)
→ Master (writes)


---

# 🖥️ 1. Install Packages

```bash id="r3b"
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip nginx redis-server -y
🧠 2. Start Redis
sudo systemctl start redis
sudo systemctl enable redis
redis-cli ping

Output:

PONG
🗄️ 3. RDS Setup
CREATE DATABASE employees;

USE employees;

CREATE TABLE employees (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    role VARCHAR(100)
);
🚀 4. Run Backend
python3 app.py
🌐 5. Nginx Setup
/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
location /api/ {
    proxy_pass http://<BACKEND-EC2-IP>:5000/;
}
🌍 6. Access
http://<FRONTEND-EC2-IP>
📊 Flow

GET → Redis → Replica → Response
POST → Master → Cache clear

